Function to get trendline info

getTrend <- function(dataset, xval, yval){
  
  slr1 = lm(formula = yval ~ xval, data = dataset)
  intercept <- slr1$coefficients[1]
  slope <- slr1$coefficients[2]
  
  return(slr1)
  
}

Plot undergraduate population vs rank

xval <- forbesraw$Student.Population
yval <- forbesraw$Rank

titlelab = "Undergraduate Population vs Rank"
xlab = "Undergraduate Population"
ylab = "Rank"


slr1 = lm(formula = yval ~ xval, data = forbesraw)
summary(slr1)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = yval ~ xval, data = forbesraw)
##

## 
## Coefficients:

ggplot(data = forbesraw, aes(x = xval, y = yval, color = Public.Private)) +
  geom_point(aes()) +
  #geom_text(aes(label = Rank), hjust = "left", vjust = "top") +
  geom_abline(intercept = int, slope = slp, color = "red") +
  labs(title = titlelab, x = xlab, y = ylab)
